[2026-03-10T01:30:37Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lu7qgwcufs5u4isGeAdHs6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary document:\n\n## Summary: Agent Tool Call Logging in Cloche\n\nI've found comprehensive information about how agent tool calls are logged and displayed in this Go codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. WHERE TOOL CALL EVENTS ARE PROCESSED/LOGGED\n\n**Tool Call Parsing Location:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go`\n\nThe `ParseClaudeLine()` and `ParseClaudeStream()` functions parse Claude Code stream JSON output and extract tool use events:\n- Lines 115-116: Tool calls are detected from `tool_use` content blocks with the pattern: `\"--- Tool: \" + block.Name + \" ---\"`\n- Lines 142-153: Handles `content_block_start` events that signal the beginning of a tool use block\n- Tools are recognized by the `name` field in the tool_use block (e.g., \"Read\", \"Bash\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\")\n\n**Log Entry Types:** `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`\n- Message types: `MsgStepStarted`, `MsgStepCompleted`, `MsgRunCompleted`, `MsgRunTitle`, `MsgLog`, `MsgError`\n- Tool output flows through `MsgLog` messages with the step name\n- The `StatusWriter` class (lines 30-66) writes status messages as JSON to stdout\n\n**Live Log Broadcasting:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`\n- The `Broadcaster` class manages fan-out of log lines to multiple subscribers\n- `LogLine` structure (lines 8-12) contains: `Timestamp`, `Type` (\"status\", \"script\", \"llm\"), and `Content`\n- Logs are published via `Publish()` method and subscribers receive them through channels\n\n### 2. DATA STRUCTURES FOR TOOL CALLS\n\n**Tool Call Content Block (from test cases in `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse_test.go`):**\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"content_block_start\",\n  \"index\": 1,\n  \"content_block\": {\n    \"type\": \"tool_use\",\n    \"id\": \"t1\",\n    \"name\": \"Read\",\n    \"input\": {}\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Available Fields:**\n- `type`: \"tool_use\" (identifies this as a tool call)\n- `id`: Unique identifier for the tool invocation\n- `name`: Tool name (Read, Bash, Edit, Glob, Grep, etc.)\n- `input`: JSON object containing tool input parameters\n\n**Log Entry in gRPC Messages** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`, lines 61-67):\n```protobuf\nmessage LogEntry {\n  string type = 1;        // \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"full_log\", etc.\n  string step_name = 2;   // Which step generated the log\n  string result = 3;      // Result code (for step completion)\n  string message = 4;     // Log content (including tool call markers)\n  string timestamp = 5;   // When it occurred\n}\n```\n\n**Unified Log Format** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`, lines 7-19):\n- File: `.cloche/output/full.log`\n- Format: `[timestamp] [type] content` where type is \"status\", \"script\", or \"llm\"\n- Tool call markers appear as: `[2024-...] [llm] --- Tool: Read ---`\n\n### 3. HOW LOGS ARE DISPLAYED TO USERS\n\n**Command-Line Display** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`, lines 249-330):\n- `cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]`\n- Filters available:\n  - `--step`: Show only logs for a specific step\n  - `--type`: Filter by log type (full, script, llm)\n  - `--follow`: Stream live logs via HTTP SSE\n- Log entry types printed:\n  - `step_started`: `\"--- <step> started ---\"`\n  - `step_completed`: `\"--- <step>: <result> ---\"`\n  - `full_log`: Raw unified log output (with Claude stream parsing)\n  - Filtered logs: Type-prefixed output (script_log, llm_log, step_log)\n\n**Tool Call Output Display** (lines 319, 326):\n- Tool calls are displayed as: `--- Tool: <name> ---`\n- Raw tool call markers come from `ParseClaudeStream()` which converts Claude JSON to readable text\n\n**Web Dashboard SSE Stream** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`, lines 672-734):\n- Endpoint: `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n- Format: Server-Sent Events (SSE) with JSON data\n- Live events from active runs via `Broadcaster`\n- Archived events from completed runs via `full.log`\n- Each event: `{\"timestamp\": \"...\", \"type\": \"llm|status|script\", \"content\": \"...\"}`\n- Tool calls appear in content as `--- Tool: <name> ---`\n\n**Log File Organization** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 682-699):\n- Output directory: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n- Files:\n  - `full.log`: Unified timestamped log (all types)\n  - `<step-name>.log`: Per-step output\n  - `llm-<step-name>.log`: LLM-specific logs for a step\n  - `container.log`: Raw container stdout/stderr\n- Log indexing via `LogFileEntry` structure (FilePath, FileType, StepName)\n\n**Tool Call Extraction Path:**\n1. Claude stream JSON → `ParseClaudeLine()` in logstream package\n2. Extracts tool_use blocks: name field becomes displayed marker\n3. Appends to `full.log` with `[llm]` type prefix\n4. Served to CLI via gRPC `StreamLogs()`\n5. Broadcast live via Broadcaster to web SSE clients\n6. Archived in output files for later retrieval\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` - Tool call parsing\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC LogEntry definition\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI display logic\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC server log streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Web SSE streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` - Message types and StatusWriter"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a070a2189c27e15ee (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57841\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 58515</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f3f88b7-a9c0-408f-9619-e3d7b92e6b51","uuid":"cf52973f-c106-4ca8-bf36-348e7b5393a3","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find where agent tool cal